Here’s your reminder that - You are so capable of anything you set your mind to!⭐️ If you see it for yourself you can absolutely do it . Don’t wait , and don’t be afraid of taking a chance . 

This is one of my favorite photos taken by @jonmacapodi 
Did my own makeup for this shot and loved the way it photographed 📸

Overlining lips 🫦 and make it look natural.

•Choose a shade that’s close to your lip color or slightly darker … I used @victoriabeckhambeauty shade #2 
•start at bottom lip outline corners of both sides slightly over lip line 
•then do the top lip cupids bow slightly overdrawn (gives a pouty look)
• fill in outside corners on top and bottom lip to give a pouty affect . It creates and illusion that makes lips look fuller 
•use your finger to slightly buff out edges of lipline to make it look natural 
• top with a gloss or your favorite lipstick ! I used @naked_sundays lip oil in salted caramel 
 
Are these tips helpful??

Let me know if you’re going to try this !! 🫦⬇️

My eyelash tips for great looking natural lashes! 👀🖤 
I’m using the @thrivecausemetics lash extension mascara currently.

•There’s no one perfect mascara for all. Makeup is all trial and error . Find what works! Try and test mascara and  different brush shapes and wands to see what works best for your eye shape!
•Use water resistant as opposed to waterproof to avoid difficulty in removing. 
•Always remove your mascara at night to prevent drying out and lashes breaking. An oil cleanser is best and most gentle . 
•Keep them healthy by using Castor oil at night ! 
•And before I apply mascara I always curl to give a little lift! 😉 

Tell me your favorite lash tips or mascara below! ⬇️
